# TopGames TopVoter Discord Webhook - Cron Examples
# 
# To use these examples:
# 1. Edit your crontab: crontab -e
# 2. Copy one of the examples below
# 3. Replace /path/to/TopGames-TopVoter-ToDiscordWebhook with your actual path
# 4. Adjust the schedule to your needs
#
# Cron Format:
# * * * * * command
# │ │ │ │ │
# │ │ │ │ └─── Day of week (0-7, Sunday = 0 or 7)
# │ │ │ └───── Month (1-12)
# │ │ └─────── Day of month (1-31)
# │ └───────── Hour (0-23)
# └─────────── Minute (0-59)

# Run every hour at the start of the hour
0 * * * * cd /path/to/TopGames-TopVoter-ToDiscordWebhook && /usr/bin/python3 main.py >> /var/log/topvoters.log 2>&1

# Run every 30 minutes
*/30 * * * * cd /path/to/TopGames-TopVoter-ToDiscordWebhook && /usr/bin/python3 main.py >> /var/log/topvoters.log 2>&1

# Run every 6 hours (00:00, 06:00, 12:00, 18:00)
0 */6 * * * cd /path/to/TopGames-TopVoter-ToDiscordWebhook && /usr/bin/python3 main.py >> /var/log/topvoters.log 2>&1

# Run daily at 9:00 AM
0 9 * * * cd /path/to/TopGames-TopVoter-ToDiscordWebhook && /usr/bin/python3 main.py >> /var/log/topvoters.log 2>&1

# Run twice daily at 8:00 AM and 8:00 PM
0 8,20 * * * cd /path/to/TopGames-TopVoter-ToDiscordWebhook && /usr/bin/python3 main.py >> /var/log/topvoters.log 2>&1

# Run every Monday at 10:00 AM
0 10 * * 1 cd /path/to/TopGames-TopVoter-ToDiscordWebhook && /usr/bin/python3 main.py >> /var/log/topvoters.log 2>&1

# Run at the start of every month at midnight
0 0 1 * * cd /path/to/TopGames-TopVoter-ToDiscordWebhook && /usr/bin/python3 main.py >> /var/log/topvoters.log 2>&1

# Run every weekday at 9:00 AM (Monday-Friday)
0 9 * * 1-5 cd /path/to/TopGames-TopVoter-ToDiscordWebhook && /usr/bin/python3 main.py >> /var/log/topvoters.log 2>&1

# Run every 15 minutes during business hours (9 AM - 5 PM, Mon-Fri)
*/15 9-17 * * 1-5 cd /path/to/TopGames-TopVoter-ToDiscordWebhook && /usr/bin/python3 main.py >> /var/log/topvoters.log 2>&1

# Notes:
# - Replace /usr/bin/python3 with the output of: which python3
# - The >> /var/log/topvoters.log 2>&1 part redirects both stdout and stderr to a log file
# - You can create the log file first: sudo touch /var/log/topvoters.log && sudo chmod 666 /var/log/topvoters.log
# - Or use a different log location in your home directory: ~/topvoters.log
# - To view logs in real-time: tail -f /var/log/topvoters.log
